A jet of flames erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set fire to a specific patch of the forest, then circled above, observing it for a moment. strangely, as it had slowed down, the odd sounds of cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be roughly lifted by a huge pink dragon!"
"Isn't it not so unpleasant, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not agreeing with Nyssi, he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws into Thassalin's back, to the point of making the Thraki bleed, but obviously, he didn't care much. That said, Thassalin had realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED A SMELL. I HAD TO CHECK."
"You had to drag us here with you?" Tenuk said as he slid down from Thassalin's back along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our strong and great fighter! How will he catch up with us?"
"He will find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's little toy car either, and if he started coming to work in a car, it's only because YOU drove us there. He just has that bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst into laughter and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a little too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINISCULE BIKE MEANT FOR CHILDREN TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE LOVED TO BE TELPATHIC. IT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CANNOT SHARE!"
Kayel snickered, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and disappeared briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel as well, their attention drawn by a clearing in the glade. Something big and black was staring at them, whistling. Whatever it was, this creature opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, without worrying about the three smaller beings on its way. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just in time, but Nyssi was pulled along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his tail's extraordinary length and dexterity, before taking off. The two-winged black creature rushed quickly after them.
Kayel sighed as he drew the gun he had on his back, then opened a pouch in which there was a belt of ammunition. He slung it across his body to have easy access to it, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to turn into something that flies?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra-powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see it to shoot it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body expanded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted back to his normal light blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb on."
Tenuk had now regained a more normal Thraki appearance, with his back covered in scales, but a pair of spikes had also grown on top, useful for Kayel to grip. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he oriented quickly and attempted a pursuit.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose it's the other big scary monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel frowned as he tried to shoot at the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his gun.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly spun around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a boon for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, and it howled in pain before disappearing again under the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to catch up.
Further ahead, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin flew in circles, firing bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight on, and the fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi used the opportunity to draw her gun, a reliable rifle. It was of course not designed for this kind of situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least deter the black beast, wouldn't it?
